                            <comment id="79995" author="adilger" created="Fri, 21 Mar 2014 14:24:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While this is useful to fix, it would not block the release of 2.6.0 so reducing the priority. I&apos;m happy that some good improvements have been made with the current patch, and would prefer that effort be focussed on fixing defects for 2.6. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="79993" author="yong.fan" created="Fri, 21 Mar 2014 14:13:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is very important to reduce the Maloo tests run time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="79645" author="yong.fan" created="Wed, 19 Mar 2014 06:17:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sometimes, create on Maloo is very slow, less than 50 objects/sec, no logs, very strange.&lt;br/&gt;
sanity-scrub in my local environment (with 2 MDT and 2 OST) takes about 770 second.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
